The paper proposes an optimization method for machine learning with Distributionally Robust Optimization (DRO) that is particularly suited for deep learning. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), followed by cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.CV (Computer Vision) since deep learning is commonly used in these fields. The paper also mentions ReLU activation and finite number of layers and parameters, which suggests a possible fit with cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) sub-category. Finally, the mention of convergence and optimization suggests a possible fit with cs.SY (Systems and Control).
